heology stem from different understandings of human nature and the proper role of science in human life. Rousseau emphasizes not just what is true, but also what is useful—psychologically, morally, and politically—for human beings. Comprehensive and nuanced, Rousseau’s God is vital to understanding key categories of Rousseau’s thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhilosophical anthropology. 0aPhilosophy and religion. 0aReligion. 0aTheology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aJean-Jacques Rousseau, theology, religion.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226825496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226825496/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles